sql:
SELECT item_id
FROM furniture_items
WHERE is_assembly_required = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS items_requiring_assembly
  FROM furniture_items
  WHERE is_assembly_required = 1;

SELECT SUM(quantity) AS total_quantity, SUM(total_price) AS total_sales
FROM sales
WHERE sale_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "best-sellers" refers to the items with the highest total quantity sold; 
- "sales volume" refers to the total quantity of items sold; 
- "cumulative sales amounts" and "average discounts" are calculated based on the sales data for each item in each store.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(item_id) AS item_count
FROM inventory
WHERE store_id = (SELECT store_id FROM stores WHERE store_name = 'Suburban Outlet');

external_knowledge:
External Knowledge: 
- "Master builders" refers to customers who have purchased furniture items that require assembly; 
- "intricate furniture pieces" refers to items with a warranty period of more than 12 months; 
- "safety net" refers to the warranty period offered with the furniture items.
